      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ALTA SIERRA (7) made a strong return after five months when third in a higher-graded race at this circuit and distance last week. Strikes at 50 per cent when second up so should be improved. Draws for a trail and if he gets the gaps could be hard to hold out. CEE CEE LOU (6) switches from Victoria where he turned in a brave effort last start, drawing on the back row and racing wide before missing by a nose as runner-up at Melton. He can measure up here. ULTIMATE CRUZA (9) draws on the back row but didn't do a bad job when fourth at Menangle last time out to follow a Newcastle win. Player with even luck. PROMISING (4) drew wider when fourth at Menangle last time out and owns a decent record at this circuit and distance.",
